i         ---------- Narrowing the Scope ---------- 		gopher.black	70
i          		gopher.black	70
iHas any of this answered christyotwisty's pertenant question? Not		gopher.black	70
iquite yet. Let's reiterate in case you've forgotten where we're		gopher.black	70
iaiming with all this:		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
i  Those who use #magick to #manifest a material desire: what is it		gopher.black	70
i  about the manifestation that tells you it's magick and not		gopher.black	70
i  Baader-Meinhof phenomenon?		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iThe question does not question that a manifestation has taken		gopher.black	70
iplace, but instead seeks to understand how you can confidently		gopher.black	70
icredit it to the magickal act rather than any number of cognative		gopher.black	70
ibiases or coincidence. To properly answer this I have to point to		gopher.black	70
ithree seminal works in religious study:		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iThe Idea of the Holy (Das Heilige) by Rudolf Otto published in the		gopher.black	70
iearly 20th century. It has never gone out of print and it has been		gopher.black	70
iabsolutely instrumental in the development of comparative religion		gopher.black	70
ias a field of scholarly study. 		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iThe Sacred and the Profane by Mircea Elliade, who I referenced		gopher.black	70
iearlier. Elliade takes up the mantle that Otto laid down and takes		gopher.black	70
iit to the next level. Notably, he discusses how the myths and		gopher.black	70
istories of a people lead to the creation of their symbols. Those		gopher.black	70
isymbols lead to an experience of hierophany, or a breaking through		gopher.black	70
iof the profane world to glimpse the Sacred and its Mysterium		gopher.black	70
iTremendum, to feel fascinated, terrified, and infinitely the		gopher.black	70
i"creature" in the midst of creation. This relationship through		gopher.black	70
iculture and symbols to find a common experience of the Sacred		gopher.black	70
icrosses all known boundaries and shares almost identical patterns		gopher.black	70
iin the Eastern Orthodox Church as it does in Aboriginal tribes of		gopher.black	70
iAustralia or the Lenape Indians in America.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iThe Varieties of Religious Experience by William James. This was		gopher.black	70
ia book written from James' lectures in Scotland on the various		gopher.black	70
itypes of personal expressions of religious understanding. There		gopher.black	70
iare many, many ways that people relate to the divine or the		gopher.black	70
iSacred, even if they consider that Sacred an unconscious power and		gopher.black	70
inot a diety. Those experiences have many things in common and fit		gopher.black	70
iinto categories that allow for discussion of the experience		gopher.black	70
iwithout having to dwell on the truth of that experience.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iTaken together these books tell a story without a narrative. It is		gopher.black	70
ithe story of a people, of all people, and our relationship to		gopher.black	70
ipowers beyond our conceptualization that we yearn for in a million		gopher.black	70
iways and experience in glimpses between breaths. The truth of the		gopher.black	70
istories that lead to these experiences is not as important as the		gopher.black	70
ifact that we all reach the same experiences once we get there. The		gopher.black	70
isymbols change, but that moment of connection with the divine is		gopher.black	70
ia spark of Truth that rings inside us and overwhelms doubt.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iChristy, you ask how you know whether your manifestation comes		gopher.black	70
ifrom magick. The science is still out, but the experience is		gopher.black	70
iredily accessible. Choose your own pathway and look for the Truth		gopher.black	70
ithat resonates deep inside your spirit. Ultimately the confidence		gopher.black	70
ithat something comes from a magickal place will come from an		gopher.black	70
iunderstanding that something has happened that is beyond the		gopher.black	70
inormal world and has pierced that layer separatating the Sacred.		gopher.black	70
iThere is a feeling in it that can be communicated and shared.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iAsk a priest how they heard the call and watch for that smile.		gopher.black	70
iThat's how you know.		gopher.black	70
